tempest/api/compute/servers/test_create_.message:
You need to have the test id decorator on each test, and should also probably have services decorators so these don't run if cinder isn't being used.

The former means adding something like this to each test case:

@decorators.idempotent_id('52e9045a-e90d-4c0d-9087-79d657faffff')

The UUID must be unique per test.

For the latter, you can add a skip check like this on setUp:

@classmethod
    def skip_checks(cls):
        super(BaseAttachVolumeTest, cls).skip_checks()
        if not CONF.service_available.cinder:
            skip_msg = ("%s skipped as Cinder is not available" % cls.__name__)
            raise cls.skipException(skip_msg)

